The 2019 MyBroadband Cyber Security Conference will take place on 21 August 2019 at The Venue in Melrose Arch and will feature top industry experts as speakers. This exclusive technical conference will focus on cyber security threats to companies and individuals, with practical examples and demos from speakers. Radio 702’s Aki Anastasiou will serve as emcee, while Sensepost CTO Dominic White, Crimson Wall founder Renico Koen, Redstor’s Shaun Searle and HP’s Maurizio Bazan will join him as speakers. Delegates will also be able to interact with top security companies, including Redstor, HP, Fortinet, and Telspace. To add further value, there will be a security challenge where delegates will put their skills to the test with great prizes on offer. There are only 73 tickets still available for the conference, and people who are keen to attend the event are advised to purchase tickets soon to avoid disappointment. These tickets cover all aspects of the event, including food and drinks.